725597f-a.text:
41-66 71st Street, adjoining the N. W. corner of Woodside Avenue, showing the yard in rear of a two-story dwelling at the above address. Shown, too, are the rears of homes fronting
on 70th Street.
P. L. Sperr  May 5, 1928

725598f-b.text:
41-50 71st Street, west side, between Woodside and 41st Avenues, showing the "Red Men's Hall," also known as Leon Trotsky's visiting place, where the Bolshevik leader frequented during his sojourn in New York. The sign over the doorway reads: "Half Moon Tribe Imperial Order of Red Men Meets Here."
P. L. Sperr  May 5, 1928
